Katy Perry may be too sexy for 'Sesame Street,' but puppets in Springfield want to make it clear they appreciate the singer's assets. 'In the wake of Elmo’s terrible betrayal, the Simpsons puppets wish to announce they stand felt-shoulder-to-shoulder with Katy Perry,' Al Jean, an executive producer of The Simpsons, told Entertainment Weekly. Perry, whose duet with Elmo was cut from Sesame Street after parents complained the singer showed too much skin, will get a second chance to sing with puppets this winter as a guest-star on 'The Simpsons.'
